                  <desc>The words Peter, Jesus Christ, God and Mary are rubricated</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1012Equestrian"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#7v" facs="010"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1030Trinity"/> surrounded by the four living creatures (a small miniature). All three members of the trinity have their hands on one orb and there are no distinct lines dividing their garments</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#12r" facs="014"/><desc>The Creation of Monday. Instruction, in blue pen: <q>“[Paint] the creation of Monday.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#15r" facs="017">f. 15r (column 2)</locus>The <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/> <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/> rescues the three young men in the fiery furnace. Instructions: <q>“[Paint] Saint Gabriel rescuing the three young children.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#15r" facs="017">f. 15r, col. 1, bottom</locus><desc>Four-fold palindrome chart on the name Ananǝya, one of the three children</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#20r" facs="022"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1101GodtheFather"/> (left), on a cloud, creating vegetation on Tuesday. Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Tuesday’s creation.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#24r" facs="026"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1030Trinity"/> surrounded by the three living creatures (a small miniature).  All three members of the trinity have their own sphere and there are distinct lines dividing their garments. Instruction: <q>“[Paint] icon of the Trinity.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#25r" facs="027"/><desc>Two charts of letters: top, nine-by-nine chart of letters described in the caption as <q>“about the wild animals of the sea” and  “about lions;”</q> bottom, eleven-by-twelve chart of letters described with the following enigmatic text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በእንተ ሶበ ሤጋል ዝመ ወተሐሲ ቆጽለ</foreign>)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#26r" facs="028">f. 26r, lower</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/> and lion (left); angel, ox, and bird (right).  Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Michael, Gabriel, and Kirubel.”</q> </desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#27r" facs="029"/><desc>The sun, moon, stars, and <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1101GodtheFather"/> floating in a cloud (a small miniature). Instruction: <q>“[Paint] creation of Wednesday.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#29r" facs="031"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1030Trinity"/>, all three members of the Trinity have their own sphere and there are distinct lines dividing their garments (a small miniature).  Instruction: <q>“[Paint] the Holy Trinity.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d13"><locus target="#33r" facs="035"/><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/> <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/> stabbing an evil angel with a <term key="sword"/> (a small miniature). Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Saint Michael punishing Sataniel.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d14"><locus target="#44r" facs="046"/><desc>Creation of Thursday. <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1101GodtheFather"/>, hovering on a cloud, pointing toward birds in flight. Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Creation of Thursday.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d15"><locus target="#48v" facs="051"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> <q>“[Paint] With Her beloved Son.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d16"><locus target="#49r" facs="051"/><desc>The Lamb carrying a processional <ref type ="authFile" corresp="AT1071Cross"/>, on a round seal of yellow background and bordered with two red lines (a small miniature). Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Behold the Lamb of God.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d17"><locus target="#56r" facs="058"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/>. <q>“[Paint] Icon of the Crucifixion.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d18"><locus target="#57v" facs="060"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1101GodtheFather"/>, hovering in a cloud, points toward a man and a woman. Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Creation of Friday.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d19"><locus target="#58r" facs="060"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/>. Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Mary with Her Beloved Son.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d20"><locus target="#65r" facs="067"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1101GodtheFather"/>, hovering on a cloud. Instruction: <q>“[Paint] Saturday.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d21"><locus target="#72v" facs="075"/><desc>An <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/> (probably <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/>) stabs Satan with a spear</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d22"><locus target="#77r" facs="079"/><desc>A man (the patron, Täklä Giyorgis) holding a book and prayer beads</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d23"><locus target="#78r" facs="080"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1101GodtheFather"/> hovering on a cloud; three <term key="angel"/>s’ faces nearby. Instructions erased</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d24"><locus target="#86r" facs="088"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d25"><locus target="#86v" facs="089"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1099StMary"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d26"><locus target="#87r" facs="089"/><desc>Three <ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1041HolyMen"/> with hand <term key="cross"/>es and fly swatters standing; one saint prostrate</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d27"><locus target="#87v" facs="090"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1049Resurrection"/>, raising <persName ref="PRS1386Adam"/> and <persName ref="PRS3926Eve"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d28"><locus target="#88r" facs="090"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1084JesusChrist"/>, hands crossed across his chest, stands before a seated man</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d29">
